From: Jakub Kicinski <kubakici@wp.pl>
Date: Sat, 15 Mar 2014 14:55:26 +0000
Subject: [PATCH v5 119/164] igb: never generate both software and hardware timestamps

Git-commit: afc835d1bda13923e3792d838dae1fa34c506b09
Patch-mainline: v3.15-rc1
Reference: fate#317388, bsc#909491
Target: sle11-sp4

skb_tx_timestamp() does not report software time stamp
if SKBTX_IN_PROGRESS is set. According to timestamping.txt
software time stamps are a fallback and should not be
generated if hardware time stamp is provided.

Move call to skb_tx_timestamp() after setting
SKBTX_IN_PROGRESS.

Signed-off-by: Jakub Kicinski <kubakici@wp.pl>
Tested-by: Aaron Brown <aaron.f.brown@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Jeff Kirsher <jeffrey.t.kirsher@intel.com>
Acked-by: Lee, Chun-Yi <jlee@suse.com>

---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igb/igb_main.c |    4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

Index: linux-3.0-SLE11-SP4/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igb/igb_main.c
===================================================================
--- linux-3.0-SLE11-SP4.orig/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igb/igb_main.c
+++ linux-3.0-SLE11-SP4/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/igb/igb_main.c
@@ -4868,8 +4868,6 @@ netdev_tx_t igb_xmit_frame_ring(struct s
 	first->bytecount = skb->len;
 	first->gso_segs = 1;
 
-	skb_tx_timestamp(skb);
-
 	if (unlikely(skb_shinfo(skb)->tx_flags & SKBTX_HW_TSTAMP)) {
 		struct igb_adapter *adapter = netdev_priv(tx_ring->netdev);
 
@@ -4884,6 +4882,8 @@ netdev_tx_t igb_xmit_frame_ring(struct s
 		}
 	}
 
+	skb_tx_timestamp(skb);
+
 	if (vlan_tx_tag_present(skb)) {
 		tx_flags |= IGB_TX_FLAGS_VLAN;
 		tx_flags |= (vlan_tx_tag_get(skb) << IGB_TX_FLAGS_VLAN_SHIFT);
